This paper focuses on the performance of network coding and forwarding schemes in wireless mesh networks, which are typically studied in the computer networks (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the results through NS-2 simulations, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of interference and reliability, which are relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories.
